          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / San Francisco, CA</p>
  <h1>Experienced Python Developer</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>PlayHaven is disrupting the mobile app discovery space by providing game developers a set of tools to effectively promote their titles for free. In doing so, we provide game players with a trusted way to discover the next game they&rsquo;d love to experience. PlayHaven has reached out to over 10 million gamers, and we&rsquo;re just getting started.</p>

<p><strong>Why you should jump on this opportunity:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>PlayHaven still has a small engineering team (5), so your code will make a huge impact.</li>
<li>Dedicated to mature, lightweight engineering practices: code reviews, unit tests, automated releases and more.</li>
<li>We love simplicity and agility in our architecture and our operation.</li>
<li>We use a modern technology stack: Python (TornadoWeb and others), MongoDB, Amazon Web Services.</li>
<li>Competitive salary and benefits, including free lunches, snacks, and drinks.</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Your role</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Drive PlayHaven&rsquo;s product and technical vision.</li>
<li>Set quality and performance standards.</li>
<li>Design, build, and iterate on core product features.</li>
<li>Construct framework-level tools to speed up and simplify development.</li>
<li>Build publicly available components to share with the community, when it makes sense.</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>How you know you&rsquo;re good</strong></p>

<ul>
<li><p>Languages</p>

<ul>
<li>+3 for any of {Python, Ruby, Perl}</li>
<li>+2 for any of {C, C#, C++, Objective-C, Java, PHP (Object-Oriented)}</li>
<li>+1 for any of {Erlang, ML, Haskell, Lisp, &hellip;}</li>
<li>+3 bonus for knowing at least one intimately from each set.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Infrastructure Musts</p>

<ul>
<li><p>+3 for any of SQL {MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQL Server, Oracle, &hellip;}</p>

<ul>
<li>Modeling, Optimizing, Joins, Constraints, Indexes</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>+2 for any of Servers: {Apache, Lighttpd, Jetty, &hellip;}</p></li>
<li>+1 for any of Caching: {Memcached}</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Infrastructure Nice To Have</p>

<ul>
<li>+3 for any of Web Frameworks: {Tornado, Django, Twisted, CherryPy, Rails, &hellip;}</li>
<li>+2 for any of NOSQL: {MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis, Tokyo Cabinet, HBase, &hellip;}</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Know This Other Stuff</p>

<ul>
<li>Security</li>
<li>Concurrency</li>
<li>Optimization</li>
<li>Memory Management</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Work Style</p>

<ul>
<li>Startup Hours</li>
<li>Startup Energy (Self-Motivated)</li>
<li>Scary Fast Learner</li>
<li>Consumer/Web Experience</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>

</div><!-- /.column.main -->

